@node "postcardware" "PostCardWare"
@next "requirements"

Convertor is PostcardWare.

Thanks go to all registered users, who registered while Convertor was Giftware. Convertor isn't Freeware!!:

@{fg shine}Lukasz Jodlowski@{fg text}

@{fg shine}David Olsson@{fg text}

@{fg shine}Sascha Ploß@{fg text}

@{fg shine}Piotr "PeeJay" Bartkowiak@{fg text}

@{fg shine}Francesco Leoni@{fg text}

@{fg shine}Jürgen Hilbig@{fg text}

@{fg shine}Peter J. Mills@{fg text}

And I won't forget @{fg shine}Stephen Williams@{fg text}, who sent me a postcard..

If you use or like Convertor or simply want to register, please send me a postcard of the place you're living in. You can also send me a translation of Convertor, look in the 'Translation' directory.

I let you use Convertor without registering just to test it, but not for years (I don't think Convertor is so complicated ;-)

I have been soo kind putting the source-code and full version on Aminet that it gets hard to find advantages for registered users ;-)

If you register:

- Your name will appear in this guide ;-) Try to be the first user to be on the postcardware-registered-users-list! ( ;-) )
- You will feel satisfied to have supported one of the remaining Amiga-developers;
- I will feel satisfied to see that there are people appreciating my work;
- You may ask to be notified when a new version is released (by e-mail);
- You might boost Convertor development a little ;-)

@endnode
@node "requirements" "Requirements"
Convertor need the following to work correctely:

@{fg shine}*@{fg text} An Amiga (no, it will not work on a PeeCee)

@{fg shine}*@{fg text} Kickstart 2.1 or better for locale

@{fg shine}*@{fg text} @{"MUI" link "mui"} Three.something (I don't know really which version, I developped it using the V3.6 autodocs)

@{fg shine}*@{fg text} with a 68000/7MHz system, Convertor may be too slow, but it should anyway work on any 680X0.

@{fg shine}*@{fg text} Mui works best with Kick3.0 or better (e.g. patterns), but this is not really required.
@endnode
@node "installation" "Installation"
@next "MUI"
@prev "requirements"
Simply copy all files somewhere and it is ok. If you want to use a catalog, copy catalogs/<language>/convertor.catalog to locale:catalogs/<language>/convertor.catalog

You can also use the included installer script. (Say @{"me" link me} if you had trouble with it and had to install by hand!)

No assigns are needed, because convertor uses the current directory.

BUT you have to cd to that directory before running it:

With toolmanager, set the directory to Convertor's directory,

With workbench/dopus or similar, double-clicking on the icon/name is ok,

but if you try with 'Execute command', it will @{fg shine}not@{fg text} work.
@endnode

